Project description

Modal Python Library

The Modal Python library provides convenient, on-demandaccess to serverless cloud compute from Python scripts on your local computer.

Documentation

See the online documentation for manyexample applications,a user guide, and the detailedAPI reference.

Installation

This library requires Python 3.8 – 3.12.

Install the package with pip:

pip install modal

You can create a Modal account (or link your existing one) directly on thecommand line:

python3 -m modal setup

Support

For usage questions and other support, please reach out on theModal Slack.
